===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|𦰋|戈|ls=ic|t1=person|t2=dagger-axe}} – a weapon striking a person's lower leg — to obliterate.

{{zh-l|*𦰋}} (“person”) was composed of an eye with eyebrows (now written {{zh-l|*眉}}) on top of {{zh-l|*人}}. The eye and eyebrows are written {{lang|zh|sc=Hani|⿱⻀罒}} in the modern form, and {{zh-l|*人}} has combined with {{zh-l|*戈}} to form {{zh-l|*戍}}.

